scene's going to be.

00:36:23.950 --> 00:36:24.940
And it's going to be awesome.

00:36:24.940 --> 00:36:25.770
Here's how it's going to be.

00:36:25.770 --> 00:36:26.936
And it couldn't be that way.

00:36:30.400 --> 00:36:32.920
AUDIENCE: So related to
that, your protagonist

00:36:32.920 --> 00:36:34.607
has to overcome a
lot of problems.

00:36:34.607 --> 00:36:35.440
So which came first?

00:36:35.440 --> 00:36:37.930
The problems that you'd have
to find a clever solution for?

00:36:37.930 --> 00:36:39.080
Or you came up with
the solution and said,

00:36:39.080 --> 00:36:40.410
how do I get in that situation?

00:36:40.410 --> 00:36:41.460
ANDY WEIR: I would
start with the problems.

00:36:41.460 --> 00:36:43.779
What I wanted to do
was have the problems--

00:36:43.779 --> 00:36:45.820
I didn't want him to just
get struck by lightning

00:36:45.820 --> 00:36:48.740
over and over, figuratively.

00:36:48.740 --> 00:36:52.120
I didn't want there to
be too many coincidences.

00:36:52.120 --> 00:36:54.360
So I wanted all of his
problems to either derive

00:36:54.360 --> 00:36:57.360
from the fact that he's
using outdated equipment,

00:36:57.360 --> 00:36:59.060
or that he's using
equipment in ways

00:36:59.060 --> 00:37:00.830
that it wasn't
intended to be used.

00:37:00.830 --> 00:37:02.910
So the solution to
his previous problem

00:37:02.910 --> 00:37:05.190
would often cause
the next problem.

00:37:05.190 --> 00:37:08.050
And so I would try to come
up with the problems first.

00:37:08.050 --> 00:37:09.610
Then I'd come up
with the solutions.

00:37:09.610 --> 00:37:12.980
The cool thing is, though,
being a writer I can cheat.

00:37:12.980 --> 00:37:15.670
